Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the steaks from your fridge to allow them to come up to room temperature.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, sprinkle over the @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Chimichurri ==

In the meantime, roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) and @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #small bowl{}, mix the coriander, parsley, garlic, @chilli flakes{1%pinch}, lime zest, half the lime juice with the @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the chimichurri (see pantry for both amounts).

Season with salt and pepper, then set your chimichurri aside for later.

== Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for both amounts), a pinch of sugar and the remaining lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, separate the leaves, then tear into bite-sized pieces. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a board. Cut into 1cm chunks.

Toss the tomatoes and avocado with the dressing. Set aside.

== Steaks ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the @21 Day Aged British Rump Steaks{2} with salt and pepper. TIP: Rump steaks naturally vary in shape, so adjust the following timings depending on how you like yours cooked.

Once very hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned and medium-rare, about ~{5%minutes}.

Turn halfway through. TIP: Cook each side for 1 min more if you like it more well done. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Once the steaks are cooked, transfer to a #cutting board{}, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins. IMPORTANT: The steak is safe to eat when browned on the outside.

Meanwhile, crumble your @Greek Style Salad Cheese{100%g} into the bowl of dressing, then toss your baby gem through.

Once your steaks are ready, thinly slice widthways.

Share the steaks between your #serving plates{} and spoon over the chimichurri.

Serve with your salad and chips alongside. Enjoy!